  <h2>How Good Firewood Habits Reduce Cleaning Costs</h2>

  <p>Burning well-seasoned hardwood is the single most effective thing you can do to slow creosote buildup between professional cleans. Homeowners who burn quality red gum or ironbark will find their chimney in noticeably better condition at the annual service than those who've been burning green wood or softwoods.</p>

  <p>It won't replace the annual clean — that's still necessary — but it makes a real difference to the level of buildup and the long-term health of the flue.</p>
